      <div class="fq-a">The plaza is in Valencia's historic centre. Metro lines 3 and 5 stop at Àngel Custodi / Pont de Fusta (10 min walk) or Colón (12 min walk). Bus lines 5, 8, 28, 70, 71, 81 serve nearby stops. The square is pedestrianised and not accessible by car.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">What buildings surround Plaza de la Virgen?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The plaza is flanked on the east by Valencia Cathedral (La Seu), on the north by the Basilica de Nuestra Señora de los Desamparados, and features the Turia Fountain at its centre — a Baroque sculpture representing the River Turia with eight female figures representing its tributaries.</div>
    </div>
